adjectives.description: pocky (comparative more pocky, superlative most pocky)

entries.meaning: Covered in pock marks; specifically, pox-ridden, syphilitic. [from 14th c.]
examples: ‘You Damn'd Confounded Pocky Whore, I am glad we are met, for now will I give you as many Stripes as I've taken Pills, Bolus's, and other Hellish Slip-slops on your Account.’
